{
    "key_findings": [
        "Structural characterization of 5-HT2AR bound to various psychedelic and non-psychedelic agonists, including DMT, revealing common and distinct molecular interaction motifs among chemotypes, leading to a broader understanding of 5-HT2A activation.",
        "The tryptamine ligands, including DMT, bind in the canonical orthosteric site, making predicted receptor contacts with D1553.32, F3396.51, and F3406.52, validating over 30 years of prior biochemical and computational models.",
        "The structural data reveals distinct chemotype- and ligand-stabilized interactions, and that different agonists stabilize varying conformational ensembles of the receptor coupled to the active-state heterotrimer, suggesting fundamental differences in how each ligand stabilizes this conformational transition."
    ],
